<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,310,1120,1146]" box="[189,310,1120,1146]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1120,1146]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1120,1146]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1167,1405]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
This diminutive species differs from the only other known Sumatran rheophytic begonia, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hughes &amp; Girmansyah &amp; Ardi" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fluvialis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Begonia fluvialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above), in its smaller stature (leaves 
<quantity box="[796,856,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
long, not 
<quantity box="[984,1088,1202,1229]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15 cm</quantity>
long), by lacking bristles at the petiole apex and having barely peltate leaves (not minutely cordate). The other geographically nearest rheophytic species from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[699,807,1273,1299]" name="Malaysia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
[
<taxonomicName authority="Kiew" authorityName="Kiew" authorityYear="2005" box="[823,1089,1273,1299]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abdullahpieei">
<emphasis box="[823,1016,1273,1299]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. abdullahpieei</emphasis>
Kiew
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Irmsch." authorityName="Irmsch." box="[1100,1394,1273,1299]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aequilateralis">
<emphasis box="[1100,1295,1273,1299]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. aequilateralis</emphasis>
Irmsch.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ridl." authorityName="Ridl." box="[189,365,1309,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="klossii">
<emphasis box="[189,297,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. klossii</emphasis>
Ridl.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="King" authorityName="King" authorityYear="1902" box="[377,605,1309,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perakensis">
<emphasis box="[377,535,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. perakensis</emphasis>
King
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ridl." authorityName="Ridl." box="[617,829,1309,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhoephila">
<emphasis box="[617,764,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. rhoephila</emphasis>
Ridl.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kiew" authorityName="Kiew" authorityYear="2005" box="[886,1132,1309,1335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhyacophila">
<emphasis box="[886,1060,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. rhyacophila</emphasis>
Kiew
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Irmscher E." box="[1147,1322,1309,1335]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="87 - 160" refId="ref18316" refString="Irmscher E. 1929. Die Begoniaceen der Malaiischen Halbinsel. Mitteilungen Aus Dem Institut Fur Allgemeine Botanik in Hamburg 8: 87 - 160." type="journal article" year="1929">Irmscher 1929</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kiew R." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref18493" refString="Kiew R. 2005. Begonias of Peninsular Malaysia. Natural History Publications (Borneo), Kota Kinabalu." type="book" year="2005">Kiew 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="King G." box="[266,397,1344,1370]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="46 - 80" refId="ref18513" refString="King G. 1902. Materials for a flora of the Malay Peninsula. The Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal 71: 46 - 80." type="journal article" year="1902">King 1902</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ridley H. N." box="[413,560,1344,1370]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="5 - 38" refId="ref18737" refString="Ridley H. N. 1917. New and rare Malayan plants. Series IX. Journal of the Straits Branch of the Royal Asiatic Society 75: 5 - 38." type="journal article" year="1917">Ridley 1917</bibRefCitation>
)] all belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[754,852,1345,1370]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,852,1345,1370]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="A.DC., 1859 (Klotzsch)" authorityName="A.DC., 1859 (Klotzsch)" box="[925,1083,1344,1370]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Platycentrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[925,1083,1344,1370]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Platycentrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differ in being larger plants with 2-locular fruits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,324,1445,1471]" box="[189,324,1445,1471]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1445,1471]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1445,1471]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[189,1399,1492,1553]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
The name is derived from the adjective 
<emphasis box="[651,767,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">lilliputian</emphasis>
(English) meaning very small, derived from the name of the fictional island nation of Lilliput.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
